Blog Platform
Welcome to the Blog Platform—a dynamic, easy-to-use platform designed to simplify blogging and content management. Whether you're an individual blogger or part of a larger team, our platform offers a robust set of features to create, manage, and share content efficiently.

🚀 Features
User Authentication: Secure login and registration system with user roles and permissions.
Rich Text Editor: Create and format posts using a powerful, user-friendly editor.
Categories and Tags: Organize content with customizable categories and tags.
Comments and Reactions: Enable readers to engage with your posts through comments and reactions.
Responsive Design: Fully responsive layout that works seamlessly on both desktop and mobile devices.
🛠️ Getting Started
Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

Git
Node.js (for development)
MongoDB (if using MongoDB as your database)
Installation
Clone the Repository

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/username/blog-platform.git
cd blog-platform
Install Dependencies

For Node.js applications:

bash
Copy code
npm install
If you are using other dependencies or tools, follow their specific installation instructions.

Set Up Environment Variables

Create a .env file in the root directory and add the necessary environment variables. Example:

plaintext
Copy code
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/blog-platform
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
Run the Application

Start the development server:

bash
Copy code
npm start
Visit http://localhost:3000 in your browser to access the application.

📁 Project Structure
client/: Frontend code and assets.
server/: Backend logic and API endpoints.
config/: Configuration files and environment settings.
public/: Static files such as images, stylesheets, and scripts.
📚 Usage
Create and manage blog posts effortlessly. Here’s a quick guide to some common actions:

Create a New Post: Navigate to the "Create Post" page and use the rich text editor to draft your content.
Manage Categories: Go to the "Categories" section to add or modify categories and tags.
Engage with Readers: View and respond to comments on your posts through the admin panel.
